==English==

===Etymology===
From {{etyl|NL.|en}} ''anergia'', from Greek ''[[an-#Etymology_3|an-]]'' ("not"; "without") + ''ergon'' ("work").

===Noun===
{{en-noun|~}}

# {{lb|en|physics}} Dilute or disorganized [[energy]], which cannot be transformed into work.
#* '''2002''', J. Honerkamp, ''Statistical Physics'', p. 298
#*: The maximum fraction of an energy form which (in a reversible process) can be transformed into work is called exergy. The remaining part is called '''anergy''', and this corresponds to the waste heat.
# {{lb|en|pathology}} Deficiency of energy.
# {{lb|en|immunology}} Lack of [[immunity]] to an [[antigen]].

